        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6685&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=New+Paineel+Necro+Newbie+Armor%21"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> <BR>The title says it all.  A brief sketch of the details...</P><P>Talk to Shwara Volerno in guild (enter building, go up first flight of stairs then turn towards center of building -- she's by the window).  She gives you a combinable container plus patterns for the various armors and instructions on ingredients.  I'm not going to give all the details here -- there's already really good summary of each piecs, along with stats at everquest.allakhazam.com.  Just do an equipment search on "abbatoir"  -- the armor's called abbatoir initiate armor.</P><P>Details on the mobs needed -- this is the stuff that Allakhazam doesn't cover.  There are three main types of ingredients needed (not including patterns from Shwara):</P><P>1) Silk threads<BR>You'll need silk theads for all the armors -- combine two spiderling silks in a sewing kit.  Spiderlings and widow hatchlings in Toxx have the silks.  </P><P>2) Woven widow silk<BR>This is an uncommon drop from an uncommon mob in Toxx, the Large Widow.  Didn't get a con on this mob -- was quite green to a 20.  I'd guess about level 6 or 7.  Drops lots of silk, occasional venom sacs and woven widow silk about once in three kills.  My guess is there are usually between one and two large widows up normally between Paineel entrance and the river.  (I never had to cross the river looking for mobs.)  Don't get discouraged if the first two or three widows don't drop woven silk.  (It took me 8 widows at first, but drop rate got much better.)</P><P>3)  Briar snake skins<BR>Yep, there are now three types of briar snake in Toxx -- regular, large, and giant.  Skins are an uncommon drop from each type.  The armor that I made (excluding robe and cap -- had better!) didn't require giant skins.  Rarity of each:  briars -- everywhere unless you really need that last skin; large briars -- not too hard to find; giant briars -- pretty rare (didn't help that the first two for me ran away and died inside of trees -- grrrr).  </P><P>Summary:  overall pretty easy quests -- took me an hour or two to get sleeves, gloves, wristband, and shoes.  Summary armor stats (from Allakhazam -- didn't see these at Magelo):</P><P>Abbatoir Initiate Boots:  +3 AC +2 Int +1 vsDis +0.70 Wt   <BR>Abbatoir Initiate Cap  +2 AC +1 Int +2 vsMg +1.20 Wt   <BR>Abbatoir Initiate Gloves  +2 AC +1 Str +1 Int +2 vsDis +0.90 Wt   <BR>Abbatoir Initiate Pantaloons  +4 AC +2 Int +2 vsMg +1.50 Wt   <BR>Abbatoir Initiate Robe +5 AC +1 Str +2 Sta +2 Int +10 Mana +2.50 Wt   <BR>Abbatoir Initiate Sleeves  +3 AC +2 Sta +2 Int +1.00 Wt<BR>Abbatoir Initiate Wristband  +1 AC +1 Str +1 Int +0.50 Wt<BR> <BR>Happy hunting!</P><P>Kalee <BR>20th Level Scourge of the Briar Snakes<BR>The Seventh Hammer</font></td>

      </tr>

